<comment type="function">
<text evidence="1">ATP-dependent carboxylate-amine ligase which exhibits weak glutamate--cysteine ligase activity. However, because of the low catalytic rate, the question remains whether L-cysteine is the actual biological substrate.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="catalytic activity">
<text evidence="2">ATP + L-glutamate + L-cysteine = ADP + phosphate + gamma-L-glutamyl-L-cysteine.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="subunit">
<text evidence="1">Homodimer.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="miscellaneous">
<text>Catalytic activity was tested towards all 20 common amino acids, but was only observed with L-cysteine.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="similarity">
<text>Belongs to the glutamate--cysteine ligase type 2 family. YbdK subfamily.</text>
</comment>
